headline: 1 Reason MSCI is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Even though MSCI (currently trading at $567.88 per share) has gained 12.1% over the last six months, it has lagged the S&P 500’s 32.7% return during that period. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
